postcontent: The KSG (Kel-Tec Shotgun) is Kel-Tec CNC’s first entry into the shotgun market. The size, shape, and design is similar to the currently available Kel-Tec RFB rifle, but the KSG ejects downward, instead of forward. The KSG weighs 6.9 lbs. and is as compact as legally possible with a 26.1” overall length and an 18.5” cylinder bore barrel. Even with this compact size, the internal dual tube magazines hold an impressive 12 rounds of 12 gauge 3” rounds in total (6 per tube). It can also reliably shoot shells as short as 1 3/4" up to the 3". This simple and reliable pump action feeds from either the left or right tube. The feed side is manually selected by a lever located behind the trigger guard.

title: For Sale:  Spikes AR15 Tactical Billet Lower Gen 2 and Billet Upper Ambi bolt, Mag., and Safty
postcontent: Features  Just when you thought it couldn't be any better we bring you this new cutting edge design. The new Gen II billet lower receiver is based off of our original Biohazard billet lower receiver but with many added features, reduced weight, and enhanced styling. If you want the absolute best AR15 lower receiver on the market then this is for you!   Gen II billet lower receiver specifications and features:   - All edges and surfaces have been 3D chamfered to reduce snagging while still maintaining the blocky billet look    - Type III hardcoat anodized finish     - Integrated winter style trigger guard    - Integrated ambi bolt release paddle. The paddle is machined from 4140 Chromoly bar stock and features a durable black Nitride finish     - Integrated ambi magazine release paddle. The paddle is machined from 4140 Chromoly bar stock and features a durable black Nitride finish   - Oversized enhanced bolt catch. The bolt catch is machined from 4140 Chromoly bar stock and features a durable black Nitride finish   - Enhanced 6061-T6 billet magazine catch button which features a hard anodized finish   - All paddles are ergonomically positioned and optimized for both left hand and right hand shooters. The paddle surfaces and mag catch button also feature an aggressive textured finish for positive engagement   - Enhanced pivot and take down pins which were designed around the lower receiver for a unique integrated look The pivot and take down pins are machined from 6AL4V Titanium and feature a grey hard anodized finish infused with Teflon for ultra-smooth function   - The pivot and take down pins have slightly larger heads and dimples in the end which allow you to break the rifle down much quicker and easier   - Lower receiver design integrates KNS Gen 2 Mod ST anti-rotation pins. Very low profile and very clean appearance   - Large flared magwell   - Magwell is compatible with all AR15/M16 magazines including the M3 Pmag, Beta C mag, and Surefire high capacity magazines   - Magwell will drop free of ALL in-spec magazines   - The front of the magwell is textured for an aggressive appearance   - Low shelf for RDIAS use   - Set screw for adjustable trigger reset   - Set screw for upper to lower tension   - Bolt catch and bolt release paddle are retained with a threaded stainless steel pin rather than a roll pin   - Lower receiver can be assembled without a hammer and punch   - 3D machined Spider logo   - 3D machined bullet pictogram safety selector markings on both sides of the receiver   - Clean milled engraving for all text and information   - Caliber is marked Multi for use with any cartridge that will fit in an AR15 magwell   - Compatible with 45* BAD ASS, 57* V7, 60* Noveske, and all 90* safety selectors   - Pockets machined in many areas to reduce weight. The lower receiver design was engineered to put the weight and strength exactly where we wanted it. The end result is a cutting edge billet lower receiver that weighs only 248.9 grams stripped! Now you can have a billet lower receiver with full ambi controls at the weight of a standard forged receiver without sacrificing any strength.  Technical specifications:   The Gen II billet lower receiver comes with the following components already installed to make your life easier:     Titanium pivot pin, detent, and spring     Titanium take down pin, detent, spring, and 4-40 set screw     KNS Gen 2 Mod ST anti-rotation trigger and hammer pins     Spike's Tactical 90* ambi safety selector     Enhanced bolt catch     Ambi bolt release paddle     Bolt catch spring     Bolt catch plunger     Ambi bolt release cross pin     Threaded stainless steel pin for bolt catch     Threaded stainless steel pin for ambi bolt release paddle     Ambi magazine release paddle     Magazine catch     Magazine catch spring     Billet magazine catch button     Set screw for adjustable trigger reset     Nylon tip set screw for upper to lower tension     These are the parts required to complete the Gen II billet lower receiver. However these parts are NOT included:     Pistol grip of choice     Ejector Spring     Grip screw     Grip screw washer     Receiver extension or buffer tube     Latch plate     Castle nutt     Buffer spring     Hammer, trigger, and disconnect or aftermarket trigger group of choice      While our billet upper receiver and billet lower receiver are a perfect match with each other, they will also work with forged upper receivers and forged lower receivers.     Upper Receiver Billet Upper- Gen II (Mil Spec Barrel Nut) IntroductionThe Spike’s Tactical billet upper-Gen II receiver is not just another different cosmetic alternative to forged upper receivers but it’s actually designed with functional upgrades that aren’t available on other billet upper receivers! We machine this bad boy out of 7075 billet Aluminum and finish it in a durable Type III Hardcoat Anodized finish. Of course, we cut the M4 feed ramps before the Anodizing process to avoid reliability issues down the road. We also flared the side walls of the receiver to eliminate accidental bolt release problems and we also machined the upper receiver in a way that lets you use the popular Magpul BAD lever or other aftermarket bolt catch levers which most other billet upper receivers don’t let you do. Because of our beefier design, it allows for less flex than forged upper receivers. We also play nice here at Spike’s Tactical and because of that, we machined our billet upper receiver to accept most aftermarket rail systems as well as pre-install the forward assist and the ejection port door. Just like how our billet lower receiver utilizes set screws to retain everything in place, the forward assist is held in place with a set screw for easy disassembly if you ever need to in the life of this upper receiver. Our billet upper receiver matches our billet lower perfectly, but it also works great with standard forged lowers so it’s fully up to you on which receiver you want to use. Get one today and make your next build the envy of everyone at the range! Features  Machined from billet 7075 Aluminum with a Type III Hardcoat Anodized finish M4 feed ramps machined before the Anodizing process Flared side walls to eliminate accidental bolt release Pre-installed forward assist and ejection port door Works with the Magpul BAD lever and other aftermarket bolt release levers Spikes Tactical engraving Works with most other aftermarket rail systems    Included  Spike’s Tactical billet upper Gen II receiver (stripped) Forward assist and ejection port door cover come pre-installed    The billet upper and lower receivers also maintain compatibility with most Mil-Spec components. So in the event you break or loose a component in the field you don't have to worry about finding any proprietary parts to get it back up and running again. Yes we did think of everything.
